  <!--   Chapter  1   -->
  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="1" style="c" sid="GAL 1" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="GAL 1:1" /><char style="it">From </char>the Apostle (i.e., missionary; pioneer of new churches; worker of miracles<char
        style="sup">[a]</char>) Paul, who’s not an apostle <char style="it">created </char>from human agency
        nor <char style="it">an apostle who exists </char>through human agency but through Jesus Christ and God,
        the Father Who raised him from the dead, <verse eid="GAL 1:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="GAL 1:2" />and <char style="it">from</char> those who are together with me—not just physically but are joint participants
        in my endeavors—<char style="it">namely</char> all <char style="it">of the </char>comrades<char style="sup">[b]</char>:</para>
    <para style="p" vid="GAL 1:2">To the churches of Galatia:<verse eid="GAL 1:2"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="GAL 1:3" />Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ, <verse eid="GAL 1:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="GAL 1:4" />who gave his own self for our sins, and gave himself so he could yank us out of this evil day-and-age
        we live in, according to the will of our God and Father: <verse eid="GAL 1:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="GAL 1:5" />to Him <char style="it">be </char>the glory forever and ever (and let us pause a moment for that to sink
        in<char style="sup">[c]</char>):<verse eid="GAL 1:5" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="GAL 1:6" />I’m astounded that you’re setting aside and replacing <char style="it">the Gospel (i.e., the good-news
        message we preach) which came </char>from the One Who called us (i.e., summoned us to believe) by <char
        style="it">the </char>grace of Christ in exchange for another <char style="it">so-called </char>gospel—<verse eid="GAL 1:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="GAL 1:7" />not that there’s another gospel <char style="it">to be had</char>—<char style="it">but I’m astounded
        at how this could possibly happen </char>except <char style="it">for the fact that </char>there are certain
        individuals among you who are trouble-makers, wanting to distort the Gospel, the message of what Christ
        did. <verse eid="GAL 1:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="GAL 1:8" />Never mind that for a moment: if even we or an angel <char style="it">who came down</char> from heaven
        were to evangelize to you something different than what we evangelized to you, let him be accursed. <verse eid="GAL 1:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="GAL 1:9" />I said it before and I’ll say it again: if someone evangelizes you with something different than what
        you received and took to heart already, let him be accursed.<verse eid="GAL 1:9" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="GAL 1:10" />Furthermore, am I trying to win people or God over to my side now? Or am I <char style="it">just </char>trying
        to please people? If I was still going about pleasing people, I wouldn’t be a slave of Christ.<verse eid="GAL 1:10" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="GAL 1:11" />Just to let you know, comrades, the Gospel which was evangelized by me: it’s not a man-made contrivance<char
        style="sup">[d]</char>, <verse eid="GAL 1:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="GAL 1:12" />nor were we taught it <char style="it">by anyone</char>, but rather <char style="it">we were taught it
        </char>through a Jesus Christ-revelation.<verse eid="GAL 1:12" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="GAL 1:13" />In fact, you heard about the way I used to live back then when I lived as a <char style="it">strict </char>Jew,
        that I was caught up in persecuting God’s church to an inordinate degree and in wreaking havoc on it,<verse eid="GAL 1:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="GAL 1:14" />and I was getting deeper and deeper<char style="sup">[e]</char> into <char style="it">the stricter practices
        of</char> Judaism, well beyond many of my peers, as I had become even more fanatical about all the man-made
        rules and regulations that were passed down to me from my ancestors. <verse eid="GAL 1:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="GAL 1:15" />But when God, Who set me apart from the time I was in my mother’s womb and called me through His grace,
        was pleased <verse eid="GAL 1:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="GAL 1:16" />to reveal His son in me so I’d evangelize him to the Gentiles, I didn’t drop everything I was doing and
        see what the experts had to say about it<char style="sup">[f]</char>, <verse eid="GAL 1:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="GAL 1:17" />nor did I go down<char style="sup">[g]</char> to Jerusalem to <char style="it">secure the approval of
        </char>the founding apostles<char style="sup">[A]</char>, <char style="it">who are my superiors by default,</char>
        but went over to Arabia instead and returned to Damascus.<verse eid="GAL 1:17" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="GAL 1:18" />Then after three years I went down to Jerusalem to visit Peter and stayed with him for fifteen days.<verse eid="GAL 1:18" />
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="GAL 1:19" />But I didn’t see the other apostles except for the Lord’s brother James. <verse eid="GAL 1:19" />
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="GAL 1:20" />(What I’m writing here for you—look—I swear to God I’m not lying.) <verse eid="GAL 1:20" />
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="GAL 1:21" />Then I went to the districts of Syria and Cilicia. <verse eid="GAL 1:21" />
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="GAL 1:22" />But I had no direct interaction or encounter with<char style="sup">[h]</char> the special assemblies<char
        style="sup">[i]</char> of Judea who are in Christ, <verse eid="GAL 1:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="GAL 1:23" />and <char style="it">the </char>only <char style="it">information they had about me was that</char> they
        kept hearing that the guy who was persecuting them before is now evangelizing the Faith which he was
        wreaking havoc on, <verse eid="GAL 1:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="GAL 1:24" />and they glorified the God <char style="it">who is</char> with me.<verse eid="GAL 1:24" />
    </para>
