  <chapter number="6" style="c" sid="GAL 6" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="GAL 6:1" />Comrades<char style="sup">[a]</char>, if a person happens to inadvertently be caught in some transgression,
        you the spiritual ones put such a person back on his feet in a prevailing attitude<char style="sup">[b]</char>
        of gentleness, taking a good, hard look at yourself lest you too be tempted. <verse eid="GAL 6:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="GAL 6:2" />Bear each other’s burdens; this is the way you meet the requirements of the Law of Christ. <verse eid="GAL 6:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="GAL 6:3" />Furthermore, if someone thinks he’s something when he’s nothing, he’s full of baloney<char style="sup">[c]</char>.<verse eid="GAL 6:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="GAL 6:4" />But let each person decide if his own personal conduct is up to a satisfactory level, and then he’ll
        be entitled to speak proudly<char style="sup">[d]</char>, <char style="it">but</char> only to himself
        and not to somebody else. <verse eid="GAL 6:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="GAL 6:5" />In this regard, each person will bear his own load.<verse eid="GAL 6:5" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="GAL 6:6" />Now have the person who’s having the Word taught to him in a classroom environment share all <char style="it">sorts
        of </char>good things<char style="sup">[e]</char> (<char style="it">materially speaking</char>) with
        the teacher. <verse eid="GAL 6:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="GAL 6:7" />Don’t kid yourselves, God won’t let anyone get away with turning his nose up at Him or sneering at Him;
        in this context, what a person sows, this he also reaps, <verse eid="GAL 6:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="GAL 6:8" />since the one who sows into his flesh will reap corruption from the flesh <char style="it">he sowed into</char>,
        but he who sows into the Spirit will reap eternal life (i.e., that special fullness of life) from the
        Spirit <char style="it">he sowed into</char>. <verse eid="GAL 6:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="GAL 6:9" />But <char style="it">on the other hand, </char>the one who continues to do good <char style="it">mustn’t</char>
        lose heart, for when the time’s right<char style="sup">[f]</char> we will reap <char style="it">from
        the good we’ve sown </char>if we don’t grow weary <char style="it">and quit</char>. <verse eid="GAL 6:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="GAL 6:10" />So then, while we still have a chance<char style="sup">[g]</char>, let us continue to do good things
        for everyone, but most of all <char style="it">continue to do good things </char>for the households of
        <char style="it">those who are of </char>the Faith.<verse eid="GAL 6:10" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="GAL 6:11" />Pay attention to the capital letters<char style="sup">[A]</char> I’m using here as I write this in my
        own handwriting:<verse eid="GAL 6:11" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="GAL 6:12" />THE VERY PEOPLE WHO WANT TO MAKE THEMSELVES APPEAR ON THE OUTSIDE AS THOUGH THEY’RE GOOD—THEY’RE THE
        ONES WHO REQUIRE YOU TO BE CIRCUMCISED (i.e., to formally adopt the Law of Moses in the rite of circumcision,
        thereby committing to following it) FOR THE SOLE REASON THAT THEY WON’T BE PERSECUTED FOR<char style="sup">[h]</char>
        THE CROSS OF CHRIST. <verse eid="GAL 6:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="GAL 6:13" />IN FACT, THOSE WHO PROMOTE CIRCUMCISION DON’T EVEN KEEP LAW (i.e., keep the Law of Moses or any code
        of conduct for that matter) THEMSELVES. ON THE CONTRARY, THEY WANT YOU TO BE CIRCUMCISED SO THEY CAN
        BRAG IN YOUR FLESH (i.e., can brag about the amount of personal effort you’re putting into following
        the Law).<verse eid="GAL 6:13" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="GAL 6:14" />But far be it for me to brag or beam with pride except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, through
        whom the world is crucified to me and I to the world (i.e., the ungodly established order of mankind
        has completely disavowed and shunned me, wanting nothing to do with me, and I have done the same to it).<verse eid="GAL 6:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="GAL 6:15" />Neither circumcision nor uncircumcision is of any significance, but a new creation <char style="it">is
        the only thing which is significant</char>. <verse eid="GAL 6:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="GAL 6:16" />And whosever conforms to this standard: peace <char style="it">be </char>upon him and mercy, and <char
        style="it">may it also be </char>upon God’s <char style="it">people </char>Israel.<verse eid="GAL 6:16" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="GAL 6:17" />Henceforth, let no one try to hassle me<char style="sup">[i]</char>, for I bear the marks of Jesus in
        my body<char style="it"> as though I’m trudging about carrying a weight</char>.<verse eid="GAL 6:17" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="GAL 6:18" />The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ <char style="it">be </char>with your spirit, comrades.</para>
    <para style="p" vid="GAL 6:18">Amen (<char style="it">so be it</char>).<verse eid="GAL 6:18"/>
    </para>
